---
const migrationStages = [
  {
    label: "Utility becomes obvious",
    description:
      "People can feel AI working in everyday tasks long before the economics settle.",
  },
  {
    label: "The first story overclaims",
    description:
      "Markets mistake visible usefulness for proof that today's winners own the mature profit pool.",
  },
  {
    label: "Value starts migrating",
    description:
      "Capture shifts toward workflow, governance, devices, records, orchestration and execution.",
  },
  {
    label: "Durable ownership forms later",
    description:
      "The real profit pool settles where intelligence meets authority, trust and operational control.",
  },
];

const captureNodes = [
  "Devices and operating systems",
  "Systems of record",
  "Identity and governance",
  "Workflow orchestration",
  "Execution control planes",
  "AI-operated businesses",
];
---

<figure
  class="not-prose my-10 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-border bg-muted/40"
>
  <div class="grid gap-5 p-5 sm:p-6 lg:grid-cols-[0.95fr_1.05fr]">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] text-accent uppercase">
        Editorial figure
      </p>
      <h3 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">
        Utility is real. Capture migrates.
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/80">
        The useful technology and the durable ownership layer do not appear at
        the same moment. That timing gap is where the bubble hides.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-5 rounded-2xl border border-accent/35 bg-accent/10 p-4">
        <p
          class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] text-accent uppercase"
        >
          Thesis line
        </p>
        <blockquote class="mt-3 text-lg leading-8 text-foreground">
          AI is real enough to destroy the current AI trade.
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-5 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-muted/40 p-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">
            What people can feel
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/75">
            Better drafting, coding, summarizing, research, support and decision
            support.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-muted/40 p-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">
            What markets overclaim
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/75">
            That the first visible leaders, pricing models and capital
            structures must own the mature economy.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] text-accent uppercase">
        Value migration
      </p>
      <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3">
        {
          migrationStages.map((stage, index) => (
            <li class="grid gap-3 rounded-2xl border border-border bg-muted/35 p-4 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] sm:items-start">
              <div class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-accent/40 bg-accent/10 text-xs font-semibold text-accent">
                0{index + 1}
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">
                  {stage.label}
                </div>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/75">
                  {stage.description}
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ol>

      <div class="mt-5">
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">
          Where capture may settle later
        </div>
        <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {
            captureNodes.map(node => (
              <span class="rounded-full border border-border bg-muted/50 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-foreground/80">
                {node}
              </span>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <figcaption
    class="border-t border-border/70 px-5 py-4 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/70 sm:px-6"
  >
    Real utility makes the bubble more convincing. It does not guarantee that
    the first market story has identified the enduring owners of the value.
  </figcaption>
</figure>
